Authorities say the suspect was arrested last night with dagga weighing 56 kilogrammes. JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested a man who was found in possession of dagga worth more than R1,2 million in Johannesburg.Authorities say the suspect was arrested last night with dagga weighing 56 kilogrammes and is expected to appear in court next week.The arrest came following investigations by the South African Police Service (SAPS), Johannesburg Metro Police and an organised crime unit.Metro Police spokesperson Edna Mamonyana says: With information gathered by the SAPS and organised crime unit, the Johannesburg Metro Police K9 narcotic unit arrested him. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)